Lazne 2013 1/2-1/2 (53)}) 6. Be2 Nc6 7. O-O $146 (7. Bg5 O-O-O 8. Nd2 Nd4 9.
Nc4 Qc6 10. O-O Nd5 11. Be3 Nxe2+ 12. Qxe2 f6 13. Nxd5 Rxd5 14. Bxa7 b6 15. a4
Kb7 16. a5 b5 17. Be3 bxc4 18. dxc4 Rd7 19. b4 e6 20. c5 Kb8 21. Rfb1 Be7 {
Sejkora,V (2325)-Jirovsky,M (2480) Czechia 2002 1-0 (40)}) 7... e5 8. h3 {
Covers g4} Be7 {White has a cramped position} 9. Be3 {Black has a very active
position} O-O 10. d4 (10. Nd2 Rad8 $11) 10... exd4 {Black forks: c3+e3.} 11.
Nb5 Qd7 12. Nbxd4 Be4 13. Bb5 Bd6 14. Ba4 a6 {Secures b5} 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 16.
Bxc6 {White forks: d7+b7} Qxc6 17. c3 {Consolidates b4} Rad8 18. Qc2 Ne4 19.
Rfe1 Rde8 20. Rad1 h6 {Controls g5} 21. Bd4 Bf4 22. Ne5 $4 {throwing away the
advantage} (22. b4 $142 $11 {would keep White in the game}) 22... Bxe5 $19 (
22... Bxe5 23. Rxe4 Qxe4 24. Qxe4 Bh2+ 25. Kxh2 Rxe4 $19) 0-1

